Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.46,0:00:14.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Four more months.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.44,0:00:15.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Four more months.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.32,0:00:16.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Four more months.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.65,0:00:17.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I bet you're excited, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.04,0:00:20.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, my, I uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.37,0:00:21.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I could be excited.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.52,0:00:22.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't really know.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.54,0:00:23.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I wasn't really thinking...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.50,0:00:24.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on. You gotta\Nbe excited.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.21,0:00:27.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, well, I guess\Nmaybe I'm a little,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.19,0:00:28.63,Default,,0,0,0,,kind of sort of excited...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.66,0:00:29.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought so.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.07,0:00:31.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. So, um...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.28,0:00:33.63,Default,,0,0,0,,why am I excited?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.72,0:00:35.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the next Daring Do\Nbook is coming out
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.75,0:00:37.77,Default,,0,0,0,,exactly four months from today!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.82,0:00:40.04,Default,,0,0,0,,THAT'S how exciting it is!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.12,0:00:43.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So what amazing, incredible,\Nawesome adventure
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.10,0:00:45.23,Default,,0,0,0,,do you think Daring Do will\Nhave in her next book, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.67,0:00:48.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Will she at long last{\i0}\N{\i1}stalk the Fortress of Talocan?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.49,0:00:51.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Only to be forced to{\i0}\N{\i1}contend with its dreaded{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.79,0:00:53.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and impenetrable{\i0}\N{\i1}arrow defense?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.76,0:00:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}And if so, could her skill,{\i0}\N{\i1}quick wits and courage{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.82,0:00:58.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}possibly carry the day?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.30,0:01:03.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Or will her next adventure{\i0}\N{\i1}bring her face-to-face{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.27,0:01:06.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}with the vast and{\i0}\N{\i1}horrible Ahuizotl himself?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.39,0:01:10.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Would she cower?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.90,0:01:11.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Turn tail and run?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.99,0:01:14.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Or would she fly at{\i0}\N{\i1}him full bore,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.46,0:01:16.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}knowing full well{\i0}\N{\i1}against all odds{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.67,0:01:18.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}that the greatest challenge{\i0}\N{\i1}she'd ever faced{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.00,0:01:20.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}was still sure to{\i0}\N{\i1}be no match for--{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.09,0:01:22.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Look out!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.13,0:01:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I'm not so sure she's going\Nto last another four months.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.51,0:01:39.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Subtitles by YayPonies\Nhttp://yayponies.eu
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.27,0:02:10.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Three months and\Ntwenty-six days.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.74,0:02:12.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Three months and\Ntwenty-six days!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.14,0:02:13.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Three months and\Ntwenty-six days!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.54,0:02:16.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey Twilight, aren't\Nyou excited that--
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.41,0:02:21.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So glad you finally made it!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.51,0:02:23.74,Default,,0,0,0,,What's everypony doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.74,0:02:25.74,Default,,0,0,0,,We're having a holiday party.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.88,0:02:29.91,Default,,0,0,0,,So what holiday would today be?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.29,0:02:32.10,Default,,0,0,0,,National Random\NHoliday Party Day.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.35,0:02:33.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoo hoo!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.59,0:02:35.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd never heard of it either.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.32,0:02:37.29,Default,,0,0,0,,But the punch is quite tasty.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.50,0:02:39.58,Default,,0,0,0,,You might say the\Nsecret ingredient is...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.68,0:02:42.45,Default,,0,0,0,,A secret.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.39,0:02:45.69,Default,,0,0,0,,How come nopony\Nbothered to invite me?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.86,0:02:47.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I came to invite you personally.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.95,0:02:50.44,Default,,0,0,0,,But it seems you were\Na speck too busy
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.45,0:02:53.97,Default,,0,0,0,,reading the last Daring Do\Nbook for the twelfth time.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.00,0:02:56.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, well, in three months\Nand twenty-six more days
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.15,0:02:57.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be able to read\Nthe next one.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.04,0:02:59.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, haven't you heard?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.44,0:03:02.08,Default,,0,0,0,,The release of the next book\Ngot pushed another two months.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.60,0:03:06.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Two more months?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.19,0:03:08.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been waiting\Nso long already,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.54,0:03:10.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think I can take\Nanother two months!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.51,0:03:11.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll never make it!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.28,0:03:14.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I can vouch\Nfor that.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.20,0:03:17.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Did they give a reason?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.93,0:03:19.84,Default,,0,0,0,,The publisher just said\Nauthor A.K. Yearling
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.86,0:03:22.04,Default,,0,0,0,,won't be able to finish the\Nbook for another two months.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.30,0:03:23.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Cupcakes?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.70,0:03:27.57,Default,,0,0,0,,How could you possibly\Nknow that before me?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.88,0:03:29.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm the series' biggest fan!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.61,0:03:31.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm just as big a fan as you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.52,0:03:34.13,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, I'm the one who first\Nintroduced you to the books.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.19,0:03:35.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.39,0:03:36.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh. Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.37,0:03:38.86,Default,,0,0,0,,A.K. Yearling just might\Nbe my favorite author.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.95,0:03:40.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I know everything about her.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.75,0:03:41.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Where she grew up.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.80,0:03:43.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Where she studied literature.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.34,0:03:45.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Where she wrote\Nthe first Daring Do book...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.88,0:03:46.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Where she lives?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.02,0:03:48.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, no...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.75,0:03:51.22,Default,,0,0,0,,though I could probably\Nfind out somehow.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.50,0:03:51.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.25,0:03:53.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you get it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.70,0:03:56.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The new book is obviously\Ndelayed because she needs help
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.45,0:03:59.18,Default,,0,0,0,,dealing with whatever everyday\Nnonsense is distracting her
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.20,0:04:02.24,Default,,0,0,0,,from spending her every living\Nbreathing second writing!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.44,0:04:05.65,Default,,0,0,0,,So I...I mean fans like me,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.77,0:04:07.49,Default,,0,0,0,,can get to read the\Nnext book ASAP!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.72,0:04:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Think about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.84,0:04:11.69,Default,,0,0,0,,We could help her with her\Nlaundry, buying her groceries,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.71,0:04:12.65,Default,,0,0,0,,cooking her meals.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.69,0:04:13.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatever.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.69,0:04:15.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Now who wouldn't\Nappreciate that?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.82,0:04:17.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm, I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.88,0:04:20.91,Default,,0,0,0,,What she probably wants most of\Nall is respect for her privacy.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.05,0:04:22.65,Default,,0,0,0,,She can always just say no.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.43,0:04:29.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Mmh... I suppose you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.29,0:04:30.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.24,0:04:34.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So how's about\Ngetting that address?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.06,0:04:50.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You see what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.41,0:04:52.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Why would she live in this\Nremote part of Equestria
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.69,0:04:55.52,Default,,0,0,0,,except to keep folks from\Nintruding on her privacy?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.70,0:04:56.52,Default,,0,0,0,,We should respect--
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.52,0:04:57.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I think I spotted\Nthe house!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.04,0:04:59.06,Default,,0,0,0,,We're super-close.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.07,0:04:59.82,Default,,0,0,0,,This way!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.63,0:05:01.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.48,0:05:05.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh no!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.44,0:05:06.45,Default,,0,0,0,,What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.75,0:05:08.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Apparently, somepony has intruded{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.77,0:05:11.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}on her privacy{\i0}\N{\i1}pretty hard already.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.21,0:05:23.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Ooowee. Somepony really{\i0}\N{\i1}trashed this place.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.11,0:05:25.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm. Maybe.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.56,0:05:26.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Or...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.76,0:05:28.58,Default,,0,0,0,,maybe A.K. Yearling's just\Na terrible, horrible,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.60,0:05:30.17,Default,,0,0,0,,unbelievable slob.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.06,0:05:33.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope A.K.\NYearling's all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.55,0:05:36.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh no! What if something\Nterrible happened to her?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.18,0:05:38.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I know! There might\Nbe no more books!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.46,0:05:43.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, but of course I'd be\Nworried about her, too. Heh.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.94,0:05:45.68,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you all doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.98,0:05:51.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh..A...K...Yearling?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.26,0:05:55.88,Default,,0,0,0,,We didn't do\Nthis; we swear!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.41,0:05:58.50,Default,,0,0,0,,What have you done to my house?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.71,0:06:00.06,Default,,0,0,0,,We didn't do this,\NMs. Yearling.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.06,0:06:00.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Agh!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.01,0:06:04.39,Default,,0,0,0,,We're awfully glad to\Nsee you're all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.66,0:06:10.50,Default,,0,0,0,,OK, clearly this\Nisn't the best time,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.53,0:06:14.81,Default,,0,0,0,,but I just gotta say how much\Nwe all really love your books.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.85,0:06:15.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Heh heh.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.52,0:06:31.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah. It's safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.54,0:06:33.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Great!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.48,0:06:36.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe now would be a good\Ntime for me to ask her
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.94,0:06:39.94,Default,,0,0,0,,how we can help move the\Nnew book along a little faster.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.27,0:06:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Chop chop.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.99,0:06:45.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Rainbow Dash, a\Nminute please.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.15,0:06:48.80,Default,,0,0,0,,A.K. Yearling has\Nmade it pretty clear
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.81,0:06:50.38,Default,,0,0,0,,that she wants to\Nbe left alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.62,0:06:52.49,Default,,0,0,0,,We need to respect\Nher wishes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.48,0:06:55.06,Default,,0,0,0,,You should tell that\Nto those guys.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.15,0:07:22.26,Default,,0,0,0,,A.K. Yearling IS Daring Do!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.42,0:07:29.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}A.K. Yearling and Daring Do{\i0}\N{\i1}are one-and-the-same.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.65,0:07:31.98,Default,,0,0,0,,My mind is officially blown.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.20,0:07:34.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Aw, come on. I knew\Nit all along.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.15,0:07:40.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.20,0:07:43.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Incredible.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.64,0:07:58.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Wow! So much action!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.84,0:08:01.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Wheeeeeee!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.91,0:08:05.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Daring Do!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.03,0:08:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Many thanks, Daring Do.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.26,0:08:22.49,Default,,0,0,0,,As you probably surmised, our\Nearlier search for this treasure
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.51,0:08:24.65,Default,,0,0,0,,was unsuccessful.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.08,0:08:27.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So kind of you to\Nfind it for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.25,0:08:32.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Give it back, Caballeron!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.41,0:08:35.24,Default,,0,0,0,,That's Dr. Caballeron to you!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.53,0:08:37.93,Default,,0,0,0,,He's from Book 4: Daring\NDo and the Razor of Dreams.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.97,0:08:39.94,Default,,0,0,0,,He wanted to partner with\NDaring Do on her adventures.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.02,0:08:41.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I know. But she\Nrefused.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.66,0:08:42.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't believe it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.70,0:08:45.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The real Daring Do and\Nthe real Caballeron!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.73,0:08:48.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So let me guess:\NAhuizotl has put you up to this.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.17,0:08:51.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You're stealing the\Nring to give to him
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.21,0:08:53.21,Default,,0,0,0,,so his hold on the\NFortress of Talocan
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.25,0:08:54.73,Default,,0,0,0,,will be good\Nfor Eight Centuries
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.73,0:08:55.97,Default,,0,0,0,,as foretold by prophesy.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.06,0:08:56.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Close...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.09,0:08:58.58,Default,,0,0,0,,but no.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.64,0:09:01.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to sell this\Nto him, make a bundle
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.35,0:09:04.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and retire from{\i0}\N{\i1}archeology in splendor.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.27,0:09:07.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Caballeron, you fool!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.06,0:09:10.08,Default,,0,0,0,,You're dooming the valley\Nto eight centuries
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.09,0:09:11.72,Default,,0,0,0,,of unrelenting heat!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.81,0:09:13.66,Default,,0,0,0,,To market, henchponies.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.22,0:09:20.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh... should we go in\Nand help her maybe?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.96,0:09:23.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh. Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.25,0:09:26.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you OK?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.73,0:09:27.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I've got this.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.48,0:09:30.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Um... She was just\Ntrying to help, Ms. Do.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.19,0:09:32.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Daring Do doesn't need help.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.04,0:09:35.07,Default,,0,0,0,,She handles her\Nbusiness herself.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.71,0:09:40.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}We've got to go help!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.83,0:09:43.91,Default,,0,0,0,,You heard her. She\Nsays she works alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.11,0:09:46.42,Default,,0,0,0,,How can we just stand\Nby and do nothing?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.65,0:09:47.77,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what's at stake here?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.86,0:09:50.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Ahuizotl has sought control\Nof the Tenochtitlan Basin
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.45,0:09:51.49,Default,,0,0,0,,since Book 3.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.85,0:09:54.73,Default,,0,0,0,,True, but in Book 4,\Nshe defeated Ahuizotl
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.74,0:09:56.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and secured control of the\NAmulet of Atonement,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.86,0:09:59.29,Default,,0,0,0,,dispelling the dark magic\Nof the Ketztwctl Empress
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.49,0:10:00.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and thus protecting the basin
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.52,0:10:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,with the Radiant\NShield of Razdon.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.18,0:10:03.50,Default,,0,0,0,,But the Radiant\NShield of Razdon
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.50,0:10:04.84,Default,,0,0,0,,is vulnerable to the\Ndark enchantment
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.84,0:10:06.04,Default,,0,0,0,,of the Rings of Scorchero.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.18,0:10:07.96,Default,,0,0,0,,But are you forgetting that\Nthe rings were scattered
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.96,0:10:09.72,Default,,0,0,0,,to the four corners of\NTenochtitlan,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.86,0:10:11.84,Default,,0,0,0,,thus rendering the dark\Nenchantment powerless?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.07,0:10:14.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Only if you assume that the\Nrings have yet to be retrieved
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.03,0:10:16.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and the ring\NCaballeron just stole
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.52,0:10:18.73,Default,,0,0,0,,isn't the last to completely\Nrestore the dark tower
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.84,0:10:20.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and its cruel hold\Non Tenochtitlan.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.92,0:10:21.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you ever think of that?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.23,0:10:25.10,Default,,0,0,0,,You gotta admit, Rainbow\NDash makes a pretty good point.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.46,0:10:27.19,Default,,0,0,0,,We've gotta help Daring\NDo retrieve the ring
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.21,0:10:29.19,Default,,0,0,0,,for safekeeping\Nbefore it's too late.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.79,0:10:33.62,Default,,0,0,0,,OK. But sounds to me\Nlike we're in way way way
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.63,0:10:34.61,Default,,0,0,0,,over our heads.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.72,0:10:37.46,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to need a\Ncarefully thought out plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.91,0:10:39.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I'm coming,{\i0}\N{\i1}Daring Do!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.02,0:10:41.19,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not a plan!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.25,0:10:45.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, come on, come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.39,0:10:48.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Bingo!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.76,0:10:50.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Here I come, Daring Do.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.36,0:10:53.18,Default,,0,0,0,,To join in adventure with\Nthe greatest, bravest, coolest,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.19,0:10:55.07,Default,,0,0,0,,most incredible hero\NI could ever...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.18,0:11:01.52,Default,,0,0,0,,OK, maybe I just need a sec.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.72,0:11:04.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Just another adventure.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.25,0:11:06.29,Default,,0,0,0,,No big deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.52,0:11:09.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Get a grip!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.72,0:11:10.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I got this.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.60,0:11:14.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Though doing it\Nalongside Daring Do?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.63,0:11:17.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow, maybe I could get my\Npicture taken with her.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.28,0:11:17.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Or an autograph.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.39,0:11:20.56,Default,,0,0,0,,There you go again.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.76,0:11:23.06,Default,,0,0,0,,She's just a pony like\Nany other pony.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.30,0:11:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,A pony who stops entire\Narmies of bad guys
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.00,0:11:28.89,Default,,0,0,0,,with nothing more than\Nher bare hooves
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.08,0:11:30.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and an attitude and
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.54,0:11:32.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Ow.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.17,0:11:33.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Ow... That's starting to hurt.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.98,0:11:34.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Aargh!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.53,0:11:37.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Ow!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.35,0:11:38.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.10,0:11:40.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh. It's just you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.46,0:11:43.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait, don't go!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.51,0:11:49.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Think fast. This is your\Nbig chance to impress her
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.86,0:11:51.35,Default,,0,0,0,,with your quick wit and courage.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.01,0:12:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I am suuuuch a huge fan.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.66,0:12:05.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Heh heh heh heh.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.85,0:12:08.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait, wait, wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.51,0:12:09.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me help you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.90,0:12:11.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I promise I can be\Na huge, huge help
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.71,0:12:13.17,Default,,0,0,0,,if you just give\Nme a chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.45,0:12:14.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.43,0:12:15.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Work...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.31,0:12:16.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.81,0:12:20.23,Default,,0,0,0,,But why won't you let me\Nteam up with you just this once?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.24,0:12:22.21,Default,,0,0,0,,My work always\Ninvolves secrets,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.44,0:12:24.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and since you never know\Nwho you can trust,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.48,0:12:26.92,Default,,0,0,0,,it's best never to\Ntrust anypony.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.09,0:12:29.05,Default,,0,0,0,,But just because you\Ncan't trust some
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.06,0:12:31.23,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't mean nopony\Ncan be trusted.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.51,0:12:33.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Look, I don't have\Ntime to argue.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.21,0:12:34.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Neither do I. Let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.50,0:12:39.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't believe I'm\Neven talking to her.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.97,0:12:48.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Looks like they decided\Nto have an early dinner
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.73,0:12:50.21,Default,,0,0,0,,before making their way\Nback down the hill
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.23,0:12:51.50,Default,,0,0,0,,to the marketplace in town.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.84,0:12:57.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I see! You're\Ngoing to ambush them
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.11,0:12:59.09,Default,,0,0,0,,like you did in Book 4\Nat the Horavian Caves.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.27,0:13:01.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Or maybe that neat\Ntrick you did in Book 3
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.55,0:13:03.16,Default,,0,0,0,,where you swoop in and\Nknock three guys down
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.16,0:13:04.93,Default,,0,0,0,,with one swing. Or maybe...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.10,0:13:07.97,Default,,0,0,0,,OK. I'll be quiet now.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.28,0:13:11.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Just watching very\Nquietly. Shh.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.71,0:13:16.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So what kind of ambush\Nare you gonna use then?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.23,0:13:19.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.15,0:13:25.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I have been led to believe
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.62,0:13:26.86,Default,,0,0,0,,you have in\Nyour possession
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.86,0:13:29.24,Default,,0,0,0,,an item of significant\Nimportance
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.28,0:13:31.21,Default,,0,0,0,,that might be for sale.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.86,0:13:35.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, um, well, I did have\Nanother buyer lined up.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.49,0:13:37.13,Default,,0,0,0,,But he's not here, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.48,0:13:39.46,Default,,0,0,0,,sounds like we have a deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.55,0:13:44.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Caballeron!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.89,0:13:46.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Ahuizotl!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.60,0:13:47.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The ring!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.72,0:14:00.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Be cool, Rainbow Dash, be cool.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.31,0:14:01.70,Default,,0,0,0,,She's got this.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.86,0:14:03.65,Default,,0,0,0,,The ring, Daring Do.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.85,0:14:05.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Give it to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.82,0:14:09.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Now Ahuizotl, you know\NI love you,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.94,0:14:13.54,Default,,0,0,0,,but I can't give you the ring\Ntill I've properly proposed.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.78,0:14:17.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.07,0:14:21.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Because my friends here\Nhave a proposal of their own.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.66,0:14:25.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Meow!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.49,0:14:34.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Bring it!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.85,0:14:50.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, Daring Do, come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.29,0:14:56.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Daring Do. I've got your hat!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.29,0:14:57.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Want me to toss it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.22,0:15:00.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Daring Do! DARING DO!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.60,0:15:06.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Aaaaahh!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.95,0:15:15.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry, Daring Do.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.43,0:15:16.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll come help you!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.16,0:15:17.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.20,0:15:20.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't bother.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.00,0:15:23.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd say you've already\N"helped" plenty.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.81,0:15:27.43,Default,,0,0,0,,What have I done?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.52,0:15:35.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Oh, thank goodness{\i0}\N{\i1}you're all right.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.98,0:15:37.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Quick. Where does it hurt?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.34,0:15:39.37,Default,,0,0,0,,In here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.50,0:15:43.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Daring Do and the ring have been\Ncaptured by the dreaded Ahuizotl
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.19,0:15:45.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's all my fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.97,0:15:50.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Dash, I'm sure whatever\Nyou did was an honest mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.72,0:15:51.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatever.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.50,0:15:52.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's just go home.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.99,0:15:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,We can't go back now!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.73,0:15:56.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Looks a might like she\Nneeds our help more than ever.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.51,0:16:00.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Trying to help is how I got\Nin this mess in the first place.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.06,0:16:02.65,Default,,0,0,0,,You were right, Twilight.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.92,0:16:04.42,Default,,0,0,0,,We should've stayed out of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.92,0:16:07.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Look, there's more going\Non here than meets the eye.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.87,0:16:10.13,Default,,0,0,0,,In every Daring Do book\Nthere always is.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.36,0:16:12.07,Default,,0,0,0,,We can't turn our backs on her.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.28,0:16:14.65,Default,,0,0,0,,She doesn't want\Nmy help, Twilight.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.09,0:16:15.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.21,0:16:17.91,Default,,0,0,0,,But she might\Nneed it anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.40,0:16:21.28,Default,,0,0,0,,No. My hero's way\Nbetter off without me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.71,0:16:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,This don't\Nsound like you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.35,0:16:25.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Where's the Rainbow Dash\Nwho would help anypony
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.44,0:16:26.53,Default,,0,0,0,,at the drop of a hat?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.82,0:16:28.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Or pith helmet, as\Nthe case may be.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.25,0:16:31.69,Default,,0,0,0,,She's here, where she's\Ngot no business being.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.12,0:16:33.51,Default,,0,0,0,,She should be at home.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.07,0:16:36.75,Default,,0,0,0,,It's fine to look up\Nto Daring Do,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.99,0:16:39.10,Default,,0,0,0,,but you've put her\Nso high up on a pedestal
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.21,0:16:41.41,Default,,0,0,0,,you can't even see your\Nown worth anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.89,0:16:44.24,Default,,0,0,0,,She's in the fortress\Nand we're here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.37,0:16:47.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And we wouldn't be who we are\Nif we didn't go in after her.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.85,0:16:49.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}And neither would you.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.58,0:16:52.59,Default,,0,0,0,,So are you with us or not?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.80,0:17:16.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Surrender now, Ahuizotl, or\NI'll be forced to take you down.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.14,0:17:25.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, Daring Do, I will so miss\Nyour amusing laughter-jokes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.18,0:17:29.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Now I must leave to commence\Nthe ring-placing ceremony
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.91,0:17:35.87,Default,,0,0,0,,to unleash 800 years of\Nunrelenting sweltering heat.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.69,0:18:09.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Gotcha!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.33,0:18:14.09,Default,,0,0,0,,You can flap too, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.31,0:18:20.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I was just about to save\Nmyself, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.18,0:18:22.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.23,0:18:24.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I just thought you\Nmight need this.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.67,0:18:30.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Have I mentioned yet\Nthat I work alone?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.46,0:18:33.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Have I mentioned yet that\Nyou're lucky I don't?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.53,0:18:52.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Drop the ring,\NHuiz-whatever-your-name-is.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.12,0:18:55.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Place the ring, quickly!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.04,0:19:02.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Get it!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.92,0:19:19.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Come with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.01,0:19:24.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Help me get all these rings off.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.62,0:19:36.75,Default,,0,0,0,,If we can remove the giant\Nring at the bottom,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.00,0:19:38.90,Default,,0,0,0,,the whole fortress\Nwill collapse.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.72,0:19:42.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Was this your\Nplan all along?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.54,0:19:44.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I had to find a way to\Nget into the fortress.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.97,0:19:47.81,Default,,0,0,0,,You did it on purpose?\NBut I thought--
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.49,0:19:51.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Didn't count on how heavy\Nthis ring would be, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.38,0:19:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Guess having a little\Nhelp can be handy sometimes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.26,0:20:07.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop her!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.60,0:20:13.69,Default,,0,0,0,,You can flap too, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.72,0:20:20.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Ponies! Run! This place\Nis going down!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.92,0:20:38.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Daring Do!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.57,0:20:41.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I will have my revenge!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.09,0:20:46.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Could never have done this\Nwithout you, Rainbow Dash.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.72,0:20:55.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I've got a book to finish!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.76,0:21:00.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Just had the coolest adventure{\i0}\N{\i1}with the coolest pony ever.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.53,0:21:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Came this close to blowing it{\i0}\N{\i1}because I got so wrapped up{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.89,0:21:06.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}in how awesome she was, I{\i0}\N{\i1}almost forgot how awesome I was.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.55,0:21:09.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Good thing I didn't, 'cause it\Ngave me a chance to show her
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.67,0:21:12.36,Default,,0,0,0,,how important it is to put\Nyour trust in somepony else.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.00,0:21:19.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Package from A.K. Yearling.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.33,0:21:20.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Sweet!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.51,0:21:23.23,Default,,0,0,0,,The new book a week\Nbefore anypony else gets it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.33,0:21:28.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh my gosh, oh my gosh!\NOh my gosh, oh my GOSH!
